    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "the scalar is not getting wrapped in a `Timedelta`, which handles all of the conversions. you can do this as a work-around. This is also the fix for the bug. PR's are appreciated. [here](https://github.com/pydata/pandas/blob/master/pandas/core/internals.py#L1697), should be like the section just below. (for `timedelta`)\n\n```\nIn [11]: s.ix[[1,2,3]] = pd.Timedelta(np.timedelta64(20, 'm'))\n\nIn [12]: s\nOut[12]: \n0   00:10:00\n1   00:20:00\n2   00:20:00\n3   00:20:00\n4   00:10:00\n5   00:10:00\n6   00:10:00\n7   00:10:00\n8   00:10:00\n9   00:10:00\ndtype: timedelta64[ns]\n```\n"
  },
